  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Jane Wigham thanks Maria Weston Chapman for her letter and the Liberty Bell. Maria W. Chapman will receive a letter from George Combe, &quot;which may be published if thought suitable,&quot; as well as two books contributed by him. Combe also sends a parcel for Dr. [Samuel Gridley?] Howe of Boston. Referring to contributions (for the anti-slavery fair), Wigham mentions especially the autographs of Joseph John Gurney and his wife. Frederick Douglass is expected in Scotland shortly, and Henry C. Wright is expected in Edinburgh in a few days.</subfield>
